dc_title_s: West Indies, the Bahamas, Freeport, Riding Point and approaches (Raster Image)
dc_description_s: Prepared and published by the Defense Mapping Agency. Depths shown by isolines and soundings. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. "From U.S. and British Admiralty charts to 1994." "Copyright 1996 by the United States Government. No copyright claimed under Title 17 U.S.C." "Soundings in meters." Insets: A. Freeport Harbour. Scale 1:10,000 -- B. Riding Point Terminal. Scale 1:20,000. Includes compilation diagram and tidal information. Map No. 26323. This map is part of a collection of scanned and georeferenced nautical charts produced by the National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA).
